# ============================================
# ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES SUMMARY
# ============================================
#
# REQUIRED (Must have):
# - DATABASE_URL
# - AWS_REGION, AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID, AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY, S3_BUCKET_NAME, S3_PUBLIC_URL
# - NEXTAUTH_URL, NEXTAUTH_SECRET, GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID, GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET (if using NextAuth)
#   OR
# - NEXT_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY, CLERK_SECRET_KEY (if using Clerk)
# - JWT_SECRET
# - VITE_APP_TITLE, VITE_APP_LOGO
# - NODE_ENV
#
# RECOMMENDED (Should have):
# - VITE_ANALYTICS_ID (Google Analytics)
# - SENDGRID_API_KEY or RESEND_API_KEY (email notifications)
# - SENTRY_DSN (error tracking)
#
# OPTIONAL (Nice to have):
# - GOOGLE_SHEETS_API_KEY (for product imports)
# - STRIPE_* or PAYPAL_* (for payment processing)
# - UPSTASH_REDIS_* (for rate limiting)
# - CLOUDFLARE_* (for CDN)
#
# Total Required Variables: 12-15 (depending on auth provider)
# Total Recommended Variables: 15-18
# Total Optional Variables: 20-25
#
# ============================================
# QUICK SETUP GUIDE
# ============================================
#
# 1. Railway Database:
#    - Create MySQL database on Railway
#    - Copy MYSQL_URL from Variables tab
#    - Paste as DATABASE_URL above
#
# 2. AWS S3:
#    - Create S3 bucket (e.g., soleblessing-images)
#    - Create IAM user with S3 permissions
#    - Generate access keys
#    - Fill in AWS_* variables above
#
# 3. Authentication:
#    - Choose NextAuth OR Clerk
#    - Set up OAuth provider (Google/GitHub/etc.)
#    - Get client ID and secret
#    - Fill in auth variables above
#
# 4. Generate Secrets:
#    - Run: openssl rand -base64 32
#    - Use output for NEXTAUTH_SECRET and JWT_SECRET
#
# 5. Add to Vercel:
#    - Go to Vercel → Settings → Environment Variables
#    - Add each variable one by one
#    - Click "Add" after each entry
#    - Deploy!
#
# ============================================
# SECURITY BEST PRACTICES
# ============================================
#
# ✅ DO:
# - Use strong, randomly generated secrets
# - Rotate credentials every 90 days
# - Use different credentials for staging vs production
# - Enable 2FA on all service accounts
# - Review and remove unused variables regularly
#
# ❌ DON'T:
# - Commit this file with real values to git (.gitignore includes .env.vercel)
# - Share credentials in public channels
# - Reuse passwords across services
# - Use weak or predictable secrets
# - Store credentials in code comments
#
# ============================================
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ============================================
#
# Issue: "DATABASE_URL is not defined"
# Solution: Ensure DATABASE_URL is added in Vercel and redeploy
#
# Issue: "S3 Access Denied"
# Solution: Check IAM user has AmazonS3FullAccess permission
#
# Issue: "OAuth callback failed"
# Solution: Verify redirect URLs match exactly in OAuth provider settings
#
# Issue: "NEXTAUTH_URL is not defined"
# Solution: Add NEXTAUTH_URL with your Vercel deployment URL
#
# For more help: See VERCEL_DEPLOYMENT_CHECKLIST.md
#
# ============================================
